div.div:
After being put on trial, the deity once known as "The Divine Twilight" is offered a job by Thanatos, king of the underworld! Now, the fallen deity is back on Earth as his former self, Lee Chang-Seon, and is tasked with sealing those trying to invade from beyond. With the promise of a fresh start, Chang-Seon is gathering the gear and skills needed to get the job done, but he's feeling some watchful eyes on him... Will this Divine Twilight see a new day, or is the sun setting on his second chance?
(Source: Tapas, edited)

The Yakmun clan, which boasted a long time ago, was wiped out in a massacre. The corpses piled up like mountains, and the blood flooded everything like ocean water. Amidst this hell of despair, Sura, opened his eyes: "No one shall be spared. I shall kill everyone. It doesn't end unless I've killed each and every one of them."
Jin Ja-Kang was the lone survivor, and with him a man's lonely revenge, which will be recorded as a legend in the Murimsa Temple in the future, begins!
(Source: KakaoPage, translated)
